In ice hockey, Team Canada wins 2012 Spengler Cup after a 7–2 win over HC Davos in the final. (Spengler Cup) (HockeyFans.at) (NZZ.ch)Borussia Dortmund score twice against Málaga in a dramatic period of injury time and wins 3–2, securing the semi-final berth. The British match officials are lambasted for their incompetence, with replays showing that at least two of the game's goals – including the winner – were scored illegally. (The Guardian) (BBC) (UEFA)